definitions.definition: A stringed musical instrument , of European origin, usually with a fretted fingerboard and six strings, played with the fingers or a plectrum (guitar pick).
examples: Learning to strum the guitar rhythmically is essential.
She was carrying her guitar in a fancily-decorated case.
The band is looking for a new guitar player.

definitions.definition: Any type of musical instrument of the lute family, characterized by a flat back, along with a neck whose upper surface is in the same plane as the soundboard , with strings along the neck and parallel to the soundboard.
